When I was growing up, my grandparents dreaded my year end summer vacation with all their being. Why you ask? Because this 2 month dark period of “vacation” made them feel incapable and old unlike everything else school related which they aced better than most 30 year old parents 🥰

They weren’t frustrated because I was home all day, what bothered them was most of my friends would eventually take off for family trips every year and I would be left behind. 

As a 8 - 12 year old child every time someone would say they have a family trip upcoming my face would fall which I barely showed anyone outside the walls of my house. It was physically impossible and not advisable for 70 something olds to take off with a kid  without any medical support obviously but the yearly tears and FOMO was very much real. 

 I once sneakily overheard my grandpa saying  how he hates himself for being old and not in his prime of health because I deserve him to be more present and how time is working against him. 

They had travelled with their children ( my mom and uncle)  a lot - Varanasi, Mathura, down south, Rajasthan, Goa etc. 

I had this irrational hate towards their memories  because I used to feel as though I missed on my grandparents youth, almost as if it’s my mistake my mom didn’t have me at 15 😂 

One trip that never made it out of my mind was their Kashmir trip, where they showed me pictures of playing in snow, taking gondolas, doing all touristy things that any next person would do. It was always in the back of my mind, and my best friends know how much I was adamant on doing Kashmir since last year but nothing was working out even when I was ready to do it solo. 

I am never getting a family trip with my parents in this life, and once I accepted it the  pain I carried through life just reduced, but the good thing is I could  travel with my chosen family and that’s what I did. 

God knows how blissful and truly one of a kind Kashmir was to me, whether it was food, the hospitality or the company. 

As much as you may not want to we just have to surrender to the higher power and trust the timing of our  life.
